rmation are refugees looking for? Who do they communicate with? What ICT, social and digital media do they apply? What are their motives to use particular devices or services, from Facebook and WhatsApp to YouTube and TikTok? Are gender- as well as age-dependent differences to be observed? To answer these questions, data have been collected through an online questionnaire, interviews, as well as a content analysis of an online platform for refugees.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 4aAsylbewerber. 4aInformations- und Kommunikationstechnik. 4aInformationsverhalten. 4aSocial Media Nutzung. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh  aAsylum seekers.  aICT usage.  adigital and social media usage.  ainformation behavior.1 aZimmer, Franziska, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1z97831107668200 cEPUBz97831106720910 cprintz978311067192640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311067202240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110672022423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110672022/original  a978-3-11-076682-0  DG Plus DeG Package 2022 Part 1b2022  aEBA_CL_LB  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LB  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK